<name>BODY ELECTRICAL</name>
<section id="1002P_S001H" variety="S001H">
<name>METER</name>
<ttl id="1002P_S001H_72ZST_T00CN" variety="T00CN">
<name>METER / GAUGE SYSTEM</name>
<para id="RM0000012GE00FX" category="J" type-id="800LQ" name-id="ME0PO-01" from="200601">
<dtccode/>
<dtcname>Fuel Receiver Gauge Malfunction</dtcname>
<subpara id="RM0000012GE00FX_04" type-id="60" category="03" proc-id="RM0250U___00007RP00000">
<name>DESCRIPTION</name>
<content5 releasenbr="1">
<list1 type="nonmark">
<item>
<ptxt>The meter CPU uses the fuel sender gauge assembly to determine the level of the fuel in the fuel tank. The resistance of the fuel sender gauge will vary between approximately 15 Ω with the float at the full position, and 410 Ω with the float at the empty position. The meter outputs battery voltage through two 820 Ω resistors that are mounted in parallel inside the meter ECU. The meter CPU measures the voltage between the variable resistor in the fuel sender gauge and the two resistors mounted in parallel in the meter. Voltage measured at this point will vary as the float of the fuel sender gauge is moved. The highest voltage observed should be approximately half of battery voltage.</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
<atten4>
<ptxt>The fuel level warning light will come on when the fuel level is below 10.5 liters.</ptxt>
</atten4>
</content5>
</subpara>
<subpara id="RM0000012GE00FX_01" type-id="32" category="03" proc-id="RM0250U___00007RG00000">
<name>WIRING DIAGRAM</name>
<content5 releasenbr="1">
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="E128091E01" width="7.106578999in" height="3.779676365in"/>
</figure>
</content5>
</subpara>
<subpara id="RM0000012GE00FX_02" type-id="51" category="05">
<name>INSPECTION PROCEDURE</name>
</subpara>
<subpara id="RM0000012GE00FX_03" type-id="01" category="01">
<name>PROCEDURE</name>
<testgrp id="RM0000012GE00FX_03_0018" proc-id="RM0250U___00007RN00000">
<testtitle>CHECK CAN COMMUNICATION SYSTEM</testtitle>
<content6 releasenbr="1">
<test1>
<ptxt>Check if CAN communication DTC is output (See page <xref label="Seep01" href="RM000000WIB00RX"/>).</ptxt>
</test1>
<spec>
<title>Result</title>
<table pgwide="1">
<tgroup cols="2" align="center">
<colspec colname="COL1" colwidth="3.54in"/>
<colspec colname="COL2" colwidth="3.54in"/>
<thead>
<row>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>Result</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>Proceed to</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</thead>
<tbody>
<row>
<entry valign="middle" align="left">
<ptxt>CAN communication DTC is not output</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>A</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry valign="middle" align="left">
<ptxt>CAN communication DTC is output</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>B (See page <xref label="Seep02" href="RM000002B6V000X"/>)</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</spec>
</content6>
<res>
<down ref="RM0000012GE00FX_03_0001" fin="false">A</down>
<right ref="RM0000012GE00FX_03_0020" fin="true">B</right>
</res>
</testgrp>
